               <provenance>ʿAmda Śǝllāse is mentioned as the
                     commissioner on 129rb, but his name has been
                     written, in vivid red and in a secondary hand, over an erasure. The original
                     owner of the Ms. might be Walda ʾAmlāk whose name has been retained on 107rb.
 The name of the commissioner and his
                     family members have been written over erased names in the supplication
                     formulas: ʿAmda Śǝllāse (e.g., 3rac, 6rabc, 7vc,
                     21va, 26rb, 30vabc, 94rab), his wife Walatta Hāymānot (90vc, 92rc, 94rab), Ḫǝdrä Mikāʾel (19rb, 21rc, 21vb, 95va), Gabra Śǝllāse (90va, 92rc), Walda Śǝllāse (Ba-Gäday) (90vc, 96rb, 99rbc), ʾƎqʷǝba Mikāʾel (95vb, 104ra). 
 In 3r-90r,
                     the names of Walda Mikāʾel (most frequently), Gabra Māryām and Sǝḥunä Śǝllāse
                     have been added, in black and in another hand, over the names mentioned
                     above.</provenance></history>
